  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "an only evil",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Lit. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "one evil",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", scarcely a “unique” evil, to which there is nothing like, but an evil which is “one” and final, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 26:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Haggai 2:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “Yet once, it is a little while, and I will shake the heavens and the earth” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 12:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "5–7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The dirge takes a fresh turn, announcing in nearly the same words that the end is come upon the inhabitants of the land",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
